The paper deals with learning embeddings from images using crowd annotations, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new model for learning these embeddings that takes into account worker biases and visual context, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the learned embeddings, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM).
